olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet dried oregano
½ cucumber
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 tsp honey
2 flatbreads
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle red wine vinegar
½ packet Cow's Milk Feta
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
2 clove garlic

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into fries.
• Place fries on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle over 1/2 the dried oregano, drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, grate cucumber (see ingredients) and squeeze out any excess moisture using a paper towel or clean cloth. Finely chop garlic.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil medium-high heat. Cook garlic until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Transfer garlic oil to a small bowl, then add Greek-style yoghurt and cucumber and stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper and set
aside.

• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• In a medium bowl, combine chicken, garlic & herb seasoning, remaining dried oregano, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Remove from heat, then add the honey and toss to combine.

• While the chicken is cooking, toast or grill flatbreads to your liking.
• In a second medium bowl, combine baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of red wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Top flatbreads with tzatziki, baby spinach, chicken and some oregano fries.
• Crumble over feta.
• Serve with any remaining fries. Enjoy!